<item>
 <title>10 Steps to &lt;1 sec page load time for a large Drupal site</title>
 <link>http://badcamp-2015.kbox/session/10-steps</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;body field&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Attent this session if you are a team lead or product manager of a Drupal site with at least a million anonymous page views a month and are interested in getting average page load time of your site down to less than one second.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is this session going to teach me that I can&#039;t learn from books on Drupal performance optimization?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are plenty of books and e-books that focus on optimizing Drupal&#039;s performance. They provide a laundry list of things to do to optimize the site. In fact, we ourselves have a blog on &lt;a href=&quot;http://redcrackle.com/blog/performance/drupal-performance-optimization-checklist&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Drupal performance tuning&lt;/a&gt; citing an exhaustive list of things you can do to improve site performance. More often than not, the reader gets confused on where to start.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based on our experience, we have observed that the requirements and methods that work with a large Drupal site with heavy traffic are different from those that work with a Drupal site that doesn&#039;t have much traffic. Quite a few steps taken to reduce page load times of a small site will not work effectively for reducing page load times of a large site. So why take those steps? As everything in life, 20% of factors lead to 80% of results. This session focuses on those 20% of factors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-track field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Session track: &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul class=&quot;links inline&quot;&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;taxonomy-term-reference-0&quot; class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/tracks/devops-performance&quot;&gt;DevOps + Performance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-skill-level field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Session skill level: &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul class=&quot;links inline&quot;&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;taxonomy-term-reference-0&quot; class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/skill-level/intermediate&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-speaker field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Session speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;textformatter-list&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/neeravbm&quot; class=&quot;user user-69 entityreference&quot;&gt;neeravbm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <pubDate>Mon, 14 Sep 2015 16:07:13 +0000</pubDate>
